Message.MsgText: PMI_INIT_ERROR=OBPL0013I: An error occurred while initializing performance monitoring for the Object Pool.
Message.Explanation: The Object Pool PMI module could not be registered with the PMI service.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the product is installed correctly and check the logs for further details. This error affects only performance data gathering.

Message.MsgText: ERR_MISSING_KEY=OBPL0004E: Message key {0} was not found in any searched resource bundles.
Message.Explanation: The message key supplied to retrieve a message is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Determine why the message catalog could not be found.

Message.MsgText: OBJPOOLMGR_NOT_ENABLED=OBPL0007I: Object Pool Manager service is disabled.
Message.Explanation: The Object Pool service has been disabled in the configuration and is inaccessible on the server.

Message.MsgText: FATAL_JNDI_IOEXCEPTION=OBPL0003E: IOException was raised during a JNDI operation.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected exception occurred binding a WorkManager/ObjectPoolManager into JNDI.
Message.UserResponse: This indicates a damaged installation. Reinstall the application server product and try again.

Message.MsgText: ERR_NO_SERVICE=OBPL0012E: Object Pool service could not resolve the {0} service.
Message.Explanation: The Object Pool service could not resolve the specified service, which is required for the Object Pool service. Review the log to determine whether the specified service started successfully.
Message.UserResponse: To use the Object Pool service, correct the problem with the specified service. If you are unable to correct the problem, contact IBM support.

Message.MsgText: OBJPOOLMGR_DISABLED=OBPL0009W: Object Pool service is disabled due to previous errors.
Message.Explanation: The Object Pool service experienced an error during initialization. The service is inaccessible on the given server. The root error should have been logged previously.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the previously logged errors. If unable to do so, contact IBM product support.

Message.Explanation: Unable to activate the specified MBean when creating an ObjectPoolManager.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the parameters used to create the ObjectPoolManager are valid.

Message.MsgText: OBJPOOLMGR_STOPPING=OBPL0011I: The Object Pool service is stopping.
Message.Explanation: The Object Pool service is stopping and is unable to receive requests.
Unable to activate the specified MBean when creating an ObjectPool.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the parameters used to create the ObjectPool are valid.

Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ERR_OBJPOOLINIT_ILLEGALACCESS=OBPL0001E: IllegalAccessException occurred when initializing the object pool. The type of object being pooled might not be public or might not have a default constructor: {0}.
Message.Explanation: An IllegalAccessException occurred when instantiating the requested object for an object pool.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the class of object being pooled has a public default constructor. If your class does not meet these requirements then create a CustomObjectPool for your class and register the CustomObjectPool with the ObjectPoolManager.

Message.MsgText: ERR_OBJPOOL_RETOBJ_INCORRTYPE=OBPL0002E: The specified object cannot be returned to the object pool because is not the correct type. The class of object specified is {0}. The expected class is {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to return an object of the wrong type to an object pool.
Message.UserResponse: There is an error in the application. The wrong object pool was used for a return operation. Correct the application.

Message.MsgText: OBJPOOLMGR_STARTED=OBPL0010I: The Object Pool service started successfully.
Message.Explanation: The Object Pool service was started and is available to receive requests.
